==English==

===Etymology===
Spanish: Canibalis: the name given by Christopher Columbus to the Caribs of Cuba and Haiti who allegedly ate human flesh.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The act of [[eat]]ing another of ones own [[species]].

